Feyisayo Popoola The Nigerian Stock Exchange has partnered the Securities and Exchange Commission to train capital market operators in the legal and regulatory requirements of derivatives trading. The Chief Executive Officer, NSE, Mr Oscar Onyema, said the workshop was organised to guide market participants to properly interpret the approved exchange traded derivative rules and recently released SEC derivatives and clearing rules. He said, “The introduction of Exchange traded derivatives on our bourse is aimed at broadening the options available to support efficient implementation of risk management and investment strategies across diverse asset classes and financial instruments. “We are, therefore, delighted to host this event in recognition of the importance of capacity building and investor education to the development of this asset class.” The Head of Department, Registration, Exchanges, Market Infrastructures and Innovation, SEC, Mr Emomotimi Agama, said the NSE and SEC had provided the platform and requisite rules to guide activities in the derivatives market He stated that it was, therefore, the responsibility of capital market operators to work with the regulators to galvanise activities within the derivatives market. Copyright PUNCH.
